proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description

Class InputConfigurationChangeable

  • java.lang.Object
    • proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description.InputConfiguration
      • proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description.InputConfigurationChangeable

  • public class InputConfigurationChangeable
extends InputConfiguration
    This class implements the abstract class InputConfiguration. It is changeable, because user values can still be added to it.

    • Method Detail

      • inputHappened

        public void inputHappened(java.lang.String value,
                 int inputParamID)
                   throws InvalidInputException
        Adds a value for an input parameter that is specified by its ID. Checks, that if batch jobs are enabled, no batch job separator is in the value, because one InputConfiguration will start one request, and having a separator here would mean an error has occurred.
        Parameters:
        value - The value the user has input
        inputParamID - The ID of the parameter that the value is specifying
        Throws:
        InvalidInputException - If the ID does not belong to an input parameter of the API this InputConfiguration belongs to

      • outputChecked

        public void outputChecked(java.lang.String outputName)
        Adds an output column to the set of output columns that the user wants to request.
        Parameters:
        outputName - The name of the column the user has selected to be requested

      • outputUnchecked

        public void outputUnchecked(java.lang.String outputName)
        Removes an output column from the set of output columns that the user wants to request.
        Parameters:
        outputName - The name of the column the user has selected to not be requested anymore

      • validateAll

        public InputConfigurationValidated validateAll()
                                        throws CollectedException,
                                               InvalidInputException
        Validates the input parameters calling InputParSpec.validate(java.lang.String) for each parameter with the value specified by the user, and the output columns by ensuring at least one column is selected.
        Returns:
        A InputConfigurationValidated, that can then build the link
        Throws:
        CollectedException - Containing all InvalidInputException that occurred during the validation
        InvalidInputException - If no API was selected
